Recently, these bumble bees **they are actually carpenter bees** have been snoozing in my mesh curtains on my back porch, which are apparently not allowed per an email I received this past weekend & I guess my lease agreement 😒 So as I went to remove half of my curtains and prepared to fight for my homebee’s resting space - I fumbled the entire flimsy curtain rod and went to get the carpenter bees out of the mesh mess. The bees wouldn’t move onto an in-organic surface and their lil legs are STICKY okay, but they walked right onto my fingertips trustingly. I actually had a rough time getting them to move onto the strawberry plant leaves. What an intimate moment to share with some sleepy bees 🥹🐝💤

Hoping to share my triumphant feelings of coming home to myself day after day 🤟🏼 

This includes, but is not limited to: 
• a newfound acceptance of my natural body (I almost got breast implants this year)
• a new diet incorporating animal protein, resulting in gaining 10lbs 🫂 #weightgainjourney 
• a new apartment with lots of lights for new plant bbs and for my mental health alike 
• new habits like walking trails daily and reading for funsies (lots of Harley Quinn comics at the moment)♦️
• a really loving acceptance of my solo parenthood journey (having so much support from family makes “solo” feel far fetched) 
• feeling proud of my success in what I consider “surface level” (physical appearance based) careers: modeling, dancing, OF
• riding the waves of my hormonal cycle with an understanding that wiping out is all apart of the fun 🏄🏽‍♀️

Harlequin ♦️ Ms. Harleen Quinzel 🖤 aka Harley fuckin Quinn 

Harley Quinn is a character that I’ve found refuge in. I’m no stranger to delusional, toxic love. There’s a lot of Mista J’s out in this world 🃏 No matter how successful you are as a woman, no matter if you have a PhD- fall for the wrong person (place, thing) and you can lose everything (especially your common sense and mental health). Watching and reading about Harley’s chaotic emancipation from her abusive relationship is freeing for me 😌 Her rage, violence, and aggression is the icing on my Aries stellium cake 💥 

I’m so in my villain era 🤷🏼‍♀️
